  "chunk_index": 10,
  "summary": "Hercule Poirot, Captain Hastings, and Inspector Croome interview Miss Merrien, the owner of the Saffron Cat Cafe, regarding the death of waitress Elizabeth Barnard. Miss Merrien states that Barnard finished her shift at eight o'clock the previous night and had not mentioned any evening plans or visitors. Miss Merrien calls over Miss Higley, a dark-haired waitress, who describes Barnard as a quiet person who was not particularly close to the other staff. Miss Higley reveals that Barnard had been wearing a new white dress the previous evening and mentions that Barnard had a handsome \"friend\" who worked as a clerk at the Coutts-Brenskell real estate agency near the station. Subsequent interviews with two other employees yield no further information regarding Barnard's whereabouts or plans.\n\nThe investigators then visit the home of Elizabeth Barnard's parents, Mr. and Mrs. Barnard, in a bungalow in Randarno. Mr. Barnard, a retired hardware businessman, and Mrs. Barnard, who is originally from Wales, are visibly distraught. Mr. Barnard explains that Barnard was an independent young woman who typically returned home by eleven o'clock using a key kept under the mat. Mrs. Barnard mentions that Barnard was in love with Donald Fraser, a real estate agent at Coutts-Brenskell & Co., whom they saw approximately twice a week. The parents were unaware that Barnard would not be returning home the previous night. Inspector Croome requests permission to search Elizabeth Barnard's bedroom for items such as a diary or letters, and Mr. Barnard leads the investigators to the room.",
